comment:
* An individual entry in the Safety Center. * *

A {@link SafetyCenterEntry} conveys the current status of an individual safety feature on the * device. Entries are present even if they have no associated active issues. In contrast, a {@link * SafetyCenterIssue} is ephemeral and disappears when the issue is resolved. * *

Entries link to their corresponding component or an action on it via {@link * #getPendingIntent()}. * * @hide

variables.name: ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNKNOWN
variables.comment:
* Indicates the severity level of this entry is not currently known. This may be because of an
     * error or because some information is missing.

variables.name: ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment:
* Indicates this entry does not have a severity level. * *

This is used when the Safety Center has no opinion on the severity of this entry (e.g. a * security setting isn't configured, but it's not considered a risk, or for privacy-related * entries).

variables.name: ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_OK
variables.comment: Indicates that there are no problems present with this entry.

variables.name: ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_RECOMMENDATION
variables.comment: Indicates there are safety recommendations for this entry.

variables.name: ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_CRITICAL_WARNING
variables.comment: Indicates there are critical safety warnings for this entry.

variables.name: SEVERITY_UNSPECIFIED_ICON_TYPE_NO_ICON
variables.comment: Indicates an entry with {@link #ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED} should not use an icon.

variables.name: SEVERITY_UNSPECIFIED_ICON_TYPE_PRIVACY
variables.comment:
* Indicates an entry with {@link #ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED} should use the privacy
     * icon, for privacy features.

variables.name: SEVERITY_UNSPECIFIED_ICON_TYPE_NO_RECOMMENDATION
variables.comment:
* Indicates an entry with {@link #ENTRY_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED} should use an icon
     * indicating it has no current recommendation.

methods.name: public String getId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the encoded string ID which uniquely identifies this entry within the Safety Center
     * on the device for the current user across all profiles and accounts.

methods.name: public CharSequence getTitle()
methods.comment: Returns the title that describes this entry.

methods.name: public CharSequence getSummary()
methods.comment: Returns the summary text that describes this entry if present, or {@code null} otherwise.

methods.name: public int getSeverityLevel()
methods.comment: Returns the {@link EntrySeverityLevel} of this entry.

methods.name: public int getSeverityUnspecifiedIconType()
methods.comment: Returns the {@link SeverityUnspecifiedIconType} of this entry.

methods.name: public boolean isEnabled()
methods.comment: Returns whether this entry is enabled.

methods.name: public PendingIntent getPendingIntent()
methods.comment:
* Returns the optional {@link PendingIntent} to execute when this entry is selected if present,
     * or {@code null} otherwise.

methods.name: public IconAction getIconAction()
methods.comment: * Returns the optional {@link IconAction} for this entry if present, or {@code null} otherwise.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
